-{"id":"flywheel_connectors-bs5ih.4.2","title":"[FCP3-V3.3.2] Add lines() method to fcp-async-core::io::AsyncBufReadExt","description":"## Goal
Add a lines() method to fcp-async-core::io::AsyncBufReadExt that returns an async iterator over lines.

## Background
serve_mcp.rs uses tokio's `AsyncBufReadExt::lines()`:
```rust
let mut lines = reader.lines();
while let Some(line) = lines.next_line().await? {
    // process line
}
```

fcp-async-core's `AsyncBufReadExt` currently only has `read_line()`. We need a `lines()` method that returns a `Lines` struct with `next_line()`.

## Implementation
Add to fcp-async-core::io module:

```rust
pub struct Lines<R> {
    reader: R,
    buf: String,
}

impl<R: AsyncBufRead + Unpin> Lines<R> {
    pub async fn next_line(&mut self) -> std::io::Result<Option<String>> {
        self.buf.clear();
        match read_line(&mut self.reader, &mut self.buf).await {
            Ok(0) => Ok(None),  // EOF
            Ok(_) => {
                // Remove trailing newline
                if self.buf.ends_with('\n') { self.buf.pop(); }
                if self.buf.ends_with('\r') { self.buf.pop(); }
                Ok(Some(self.buf.clone()))
            }
            Err(e) => Err(e),
        }
    }
}

// Add to AsyncBufReadExt trait:
fn lines(self) -> Lines<Self> where Self: Sized {
    Lines { reader: self, buf: String::new() }
}
```

## Acceptance criteria
- `reader.lines().next_line().await` works identically to tokio's pattern
- EOF returns Ok(None)
- Newline characters stripped from returned strings
- Works with both \n and \r\n line endings

## Testing
- Test: empty reader → next_line returns None
- Test: single line → returns line, then None
- Test: multiple lines → returns each, then None
- Test: line with \r\n → \r stripped
- Test: line without trailing newline (EOF) → returned correctly","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-14T21:45:28.001255Z","created_by":"BeigeCave","updated_at":"2026-03-14T23:00:20.667029Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["async-core","fcp3","v3"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-bs5ih.4.2","depends_on_id":"flywheel_connectors-bs5ih.2","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-14T21:59:55.839772Z","created_by":"BeigeCave","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"closed_at":"2026-03-15T00:54:23.775800+00:00","close_reason":"Lines struct with next_line() already implemented at fcp-async-core::io lines 1871+. Wraps asupersync::io::Lines. Done by concurrent agent."}
